You can install Node.js anywhere, I installed mine in my user folder ( ~/ )

Install Node.js with MySQL support

Mac
git clone --depth 1 git://github.com/joyent/node.git
cd node
git checkout origin/v0.4     (0.4 is current stable, 0.5 is master and is unstable)
export JOBS=2           (optional, sets number of parallel commands)
mkdir ~/local
./configure --prefix=$HOME/local/node
make
make install
echo 'export PATH=$HOME/local/node/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.profile
source ~/.profile
curl http://npmjs.org/install.sh | sh
cd ~/local/node/lib
npm install mysql

Windows (Not tested)
Binary File: http://node-js.prcn.co.cc/
NPM installed?